					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="1361261"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1386781863 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Dec 2013 17:11</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1913288">
									

<p>One of the criteria I use for voting is accessibility to a new reader. Usually, if a piece requires you to have read an asston of other, non-related articles on the site, I'm disinclined to stay away from the downvote button. More so if you also need to have kept up on site culture to really get anything, and even more so if the piece is specifically referencing current site events at the time.</p>
<p>The more articles that appear on this site that rely on poorly-aging commentary on whatever is going on at the wiki at the moment and references that require links to ten different articles to understand, the closer we get to being yet another fanwank watering hole.</p>

