														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1913307">
									

<p>I lurked on this site a long time before I joined. Articles like the Sword of Damocles and the most terrible thing in the world were still on the main list and in the positives when I first started reading. I was doing a research paper on Baba Yaga for a mythology class and stumbled on the article Gears wrote. So I understand the desire to reference fun stuff from the past and the interesting in jokes that go along with that. I have to agree with Kalinin that it isn't really fair to the newer members to expect them to know what the hell a lot of these type of articles are talking about. When was the last time Dr. Glass was even in a tale? Unfinished business maybe? Which isn't exactly a spring chicken of a tale itself. It would probably be helpful if there were some footnotes that would lead people to some of the more obscure references made in tales like this.</p>

							</div>

								
					
